{
  "text": "Higher levels of religiosity and spirituality in adolescents have been associated with better mental health (6), a reduction in the negative effects of psychiatric disorders on suicidal thoughts [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and protective effects for the emotional and physical well-being of adolescents exposed to traumatic events [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
